  <span id="freeText17809653446780636516" style="display:none">A very complex book. One of the really great books that I've read. While the story is technically historical fiction since he adds various pieces that are missing to historian, this is really a detailed analysis of the grand strategy of the first half of the civil war. It is also an extremely insightful look into the politics and the extremely difficult position of Lincoln during the start of his administration. finally this book also gives a detailed treatment of many key people during the civil war, mainly but not exclusively political figures.</span>
