<div id="review_140134679" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/140134679" />
    <a title="Fast Primes" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1135552-fast-primes"><img alt="Fast Primes" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/m_50x66-82093808bca726cb3249a493fbd3bd0f.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/140134679?book_show_action=true">Jan 11, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Fast Primes" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Fast Primes" href="/user/show/1135552-fast-primes">Fast Primes</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer140134679" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer956270531488318952">This is an outstanding novel of the American Civil War--some 1400 pages long (of which 200 pages are footnotes, explanations and bibliography). The focus of the book is the political and legal machinations of the war--not the military battles. My only caveat is that it ends with the signing of the emancipation proclamation. Still this is a 5 star work.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


