<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer6219527013715229816">William Lewis Safire was an American author, columnist, journalist and presidential speechwriter.<br/><br/>He was perhaps best known as a long-time syndicated political columnist for the <i>New York Times</i> and a regular contributor to &quot;On Language&quot; in the <i>New York Times Magazine</i>, a column on popular etymology, new or unusual usages, and other language-related topics.<br/></span>
  <span id="freeText6219527013715229816" style="display:none">William Lewis Safire was an American author, columnist, journalist and presidential speechwriter.<br /><br />He was perhaps best known as a long-time syndicated political columnist for the <i>New York Times</i> and a regular contributor to "On Language" in the <i>New York Times Magazine</i>, a column on popular etymology, new or unusual usages, and other language-related topics.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="6219527013715229816" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

</div>
